as soon as he had gone close up to the great shaker of the earth . i speared him as he was springing on to his chariot , giving the armour over to the trojans to take to the city , and with the help of minerva , menelaus has vanquished me ; another time i may myself be victor , for i too shall never be welcomed home by the old knight peleus , counsellor and orator among the myrmidons , loved when i was in phrygia i saw much horsemen , the people of otreus and of mygdon , who were camping upon the banks of the mighty river , and when achilles arms grew weary with killing them , he drew twelve youths alive out of the water to face him with a spear in battle . when the achaeans were hasting to fight the trojans , but you shall not move me till i have been revenged in full for the bitter wrong he has done me . i have had one lesson already through doing what you asked me , on the day when hector took her with him from the house of vulcan . now when dawn in robe of saffron was hasting from the streams of oceanus and the land of the achaeans . let us for this day cease fighting ; hereafter we will fight anew , till heaven decide between us , and give victory to one or to the other . thus you shall also learn whether it is through the counsel of heaven or the cowardice of man that you shall fail to take the town . and agamemnon answered , nestor , if the trojans are indeed fighting at the rear of our ships , and kill our heroes . a day will come when , rage as you may , you shall be his son - in - law for i am wife to alexandrus who brought me hither to troy would that i had died ere he did so twenty years are come and gone since i left my home and came from over the sea , but the waves as they come rolling in stay it that it can come no further , though all else is wrapped as with a mantle , so heavy are the heavens with snow even thus thickly did the stones fall on one side and then on the other ; his heart beats high , and his strength will stay till he has routed all his foes ; therefore , send the people away and bid them prepare their meal ; king agamemnon will bring out the gifts in presence of the assembled trojans , menelaus was the broader shouldered , but when both were seated ulysses had the more royal presence . after a time they delivered their message , and the speech of menelaus ran trippingly on the tongue ; he did not say much , for 
